# Long Images - Progressive JPEG

When the user adds new long images (`*_long.jpg`) to the `public/` folder, always run:

```bash
npm run make-progressive
```

This converts them to progressive JPEGs so they load top-to-bottom for a better UX. The script auto-detects all `*_long.jpg` files in `public/`, so no manual updates are needed.
